We used to be 11, now we are 7 In a far-off land, there lived 11 brave chickenoids. They were a group of intelligent and resourceful chickens who spent their days foraging for food and enjoying each other's company. But little did they know that four merciless wolves were watching their every move, waiting for the perfect moment to strike. One day, while the chickenoids were out gathering food, the wolves attacked. They swooped in, snatching up four of the chickenoids and carrying them off into the woods. The remaining seven chickens were left shaken and scared, wondering what they should do next. But as they huddled together, they began to realize that they couldn't just sit back and let the wolves have their way. They had to fight back. And so, they began to plot and plan. Over the next few days, the chickenoids worked tirelessly to prepare for battle. They gathered weapons, set traps, and trained themselves in the art of combat. Finally, they felt ready to take on the wolves. The day of the battle arrived, and the chickenoids marched bravely into the woods, determined to protect their home and their friends. They could hear the wolves snarling in the distance, but they didn't let their fear show. As they crept closer and closer to the wolves' lair, they suddenly heard a loud roar. The wolves had spotted them, and they were coming for them fast. The chickenoids fought bravely, using all the skills they had learned in their training. They dodged and weaved, striking back at the wolves with all their might. It was a fierce battle, but the chickenoids refused to back down. In the end, seven chickenoids emerged from the woods, battered and bruised, but alive. The other four had died fighting for their home and their friends. The wolves were nowhere to be seen. Had they fled, or had they been defeated? The chickenoids didn't know for sure, but they didn't care. They had stood up for themselves and fought back against their enemies, and that was all that mattered. From that day on, the chickenoids were more vigilant than ever, always watching out for the wolves who might try to harm them. But they also knew that they were strong and brave, and that they could overcome any obstacle if they worked together. (edited)

Once upon a time in a faraway land, there was a small village where 7 chickenoids roamed freely. Chickenoids were half-chicken, half-human creatures who lived in harmony with humans and other animals. One day, a werewolf appeared in the village, causing chaos and destruction. The chickenoids tried to escape but were cornered by the werewolf at the edge of a steep cliff. In a desperate attempt to save themselves, one of the chickenoids jumped off the cliff. As it fell, the chickenoid saw a shimmering portal open up in the air below. It landed in the portal, which closed just as quickly as it had opened. The chickenoid found itself in a strange, otherworldly dimension. It looked around in wonder and amazement but soon realized that it was not alone. The dimension was inhabited by all sorts of creatures, some friendly, some not. The chickenoid tried to communicate with them but found that they spoke in a language it did not understand. Days turned into weeks, and the chickenoid began to miss its old life in the village. It longed to return home and be with its friends and family. One day, it stumbled upon a portal that led back to its world. The chickenoid stepped through the portal and found itself back in the village. It looked around, relieved to see that the werewolf was gone. Then it searched the place and noticed that everyone and everything was gone, there were only ruins dated from 3000 years ago. Oh oh. As she continued to explore, she came across a group of friendly creatures who offered to help her.
